quran[32]{c,v,t}:
  1,1,IN the name of the merciful and compassionate God
  1,2,"Praise belongs to God, the Lord of the worlds"
  1,3,"the merciful, the compassionate"
  1,4,the ruler of the day of judgment
  1,5,Thee we serve and Thee we ask for aid
  1,6,Guide us in the right path
  1,7,the path of those Thou art gracious to; not of those Thou art wroth with; nor of those who err
  2,1,ALIF LAM MIM
  2,2,That is the book! there is no doubt therein; a guide to the pious
  2,3,"who believe in the unseen, and are steadfast in prayer, and of what we have given them expend in alms"
  2,4,"who believe in what is revealed to thee, and what was revealed before thee, and of the hereafter they are sure"
  2,5,"These are in guidance from their Lord, and these are the prosperous"
  2,6,"Verily, those who misbelieve, it is the same to them if ye warn them or if ye warn them not, they will not believe"
  2,7,"God has set a seal upon their hearts and on their hearing; and on their eyes is dimness, and for them is grievous woe"
  2,8,"And there are those among men who say, 'We believe in God and in the last day;' but they do not believe"
  2,9,They would deceive God and those who do believe; but they deceive only themselves and they do not perceive
  2,10,"In their hearts is a sickness, and God has made them still more sick, and for them is grievous woe because they lied"
  2,11,"And when it is said to them, 'Do not evil in the earth,' they say, 'We do but what is right"
  2,12,Are not they the evildoers? and yet they do not perceive
  2,13,"And when it is said to them, 'Believe as other men believe,' they say, 'Shall we believe as fools believe?' Are not they themselves the fools? and yet they do not know"
  2,14,"And when they meet those who believe, they say, 'We do believe;' but when they go aside with their devils, they say, 'We are with you; we were but mocking"
  2,15,"God shall mock at them and let them go on in their rebellion, blindly wandering on"
  2,16,"Those who buy error for guidance, their traffic profits not, and they are not guided"
  2,17,"Their likeness is as the likeness of one who kindles a fire; and when it lights up all around, God goes off with their light, and leaves them in darkness that they cannot see"
  2,18,"Deafness, dumbness, blindness, and they shall not return"
  2,19,"Or like a storm-cloud from the sky, wherein is darkness and thunder and lightning; they put their fingers in their ears at the thunder-clap, for fear of death, for God encompasses the misbelievers"
  2,20,"The lightning well-nigh snatches off their sight, whenever it shines for them they walk therein; but when it is dark for them they halt; and if God willed He would go off with their hearing and their sight; verily, God is mighty over all"
  2,21,O ye folk! serve your Lord who created you and those before you; haply ye may fear
  2,22,"who made the earth for you a bed and the heaven a dome; and sent down from heaven water, and brought forth therewith fruits as a sustenance for you; so make no peers for God, the while ye know"
  2,23,"And if ye are in doubt of what we have revealed unto our servant, then bring a chapter like it, and call your witnesses other than God if ye tell truth"
  2,24,"But if ye do it not, and ye shall surely do it not, then fear the fire whose fuel is men and stones, prepared for misbelievers"
  2,25,"But bear the glad tidings to those who believe and work righteousness, that for them are gardens beneath which rivers flow; whenever they are provided with fruit therefrom they say, 'This is what we were provided with before,' and they shall be provided with the like; and there are pure wives for them therein, and they shall dwell therein for aye"